<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She recently had her heart broken in front of the nation on The Bachelor.</p>

<p>But Bella Varelis is wasting no time dwelling on her brutal dumping by Locky Gilbert, as she's now signed with a top talent agency to further her career as an influencer.</p>

<p>The 25-year-old aspiring socialite is being represented by MAXCONNECTORS, which already has the likes of Nikki Phillips and Natalie Roser on its books.</p>

<p>Moving on! The Bachelor's Bella Varelis (pictured) is wasting no time dwelling on her brutal dumping by Locky Gilbert, as she's now signed with a top influencer talent agency</p>

<p>MAXCONNECTORS announced it had signed Bella on Tuesday.</p>

<p>Alongside a shout-out for collaborations, the agency wrote: 'Down-to-earth Bella radiates warmth, happiness and health, speaking to a life of love, fun and adventure.'</p>

<p>And it appears Bella is just as keen to make her 15 minutes of fame more permanent. </p>

<p>Boosting her profile: The 25-year-old aspiring socialite is being represented by MAXCONNECTORS, which already has the likes of Nikki Phillips and Natalie Roser on its books</p>

<p>To her own 108,000 followers, Bella wrote: 'Over the moon to finally announce that I'm officially a part of the incredible MAXCONNECTORS family!</p>

<p>'So excited to see what the future holds and stoked to be represented by this beautiful team!'</p>

<p>While Bella currently has a modest number of followers, others represented by the agency have millions watching their every move.</p>

<p>MAXCONNECTORS' most popular client, YouTube beauty queen Lauren Curtis, has 1.3 million Instagram followers and more than three million YouTube subscribers.</p>

<p>Heartbroken: Bella was brutally dumped in front of the nation by Locky Gilbert (right) during the season finale of The Bachelor last week </p>

<p>In more promising news for Bella's career, she is rumoured to be appearing on the upcoming season of Bachelor in Paradise - after losing Locky's heart to her former best friend Irena Srbinovska.</p>

<p>Discussing last week's Bachelor finale on Channel 10's Cocktails and Roses podcast, franchise host Osher Günsberg said: 'Maybe it's not the last we'll see of Bella.'</p>

<p>'I don't know if we're going to go back at any point, but part of me really wants to say "bula Bella" under a bure - but I don't know if we're going to do Paradise in Fiji at the moment. I don't know what's going to happen,' he added.</p>

<p>The One! Irena Srbinovska (left) won Locky's heart, leaving her former best friend devastated</p>
